```python
def find_next_activity(past_traces, prefix):
    # Define attribute abbreviations
    attr_map = {
       'syus':'syn:username',
       'syuu':'syn:uuid',
        'titi': 'time:timestamp',
        'A2': 'A2.1',
        'A7': 'A7.1'
    }

    # Iterate over each past trace
    for trace in past_traces:
        # Check if the trace matches the prefix
        if all([trace[i] == prefix[i] for i in range(len(prefix))]):
            # Extract the next activity
            next_activity = trace[-1]
            return next_activity


past_traces = [
    ["START+complete", "A1+complete", "A2+complete", "bE1+complete", "bA11+complete", "bA2+complete", "A3+complete", "tE1+complete", "tA9+complete", "tA2+complete", "A4+complete"],
    ["START+complete", "A1+complete", "A2+complete", "bE1+complete", "bA9+complete", "bA2+complete", "A3+complete", "tE1+complete", "tA11+complete", "tA2+complete", "A4+complete"],
    ["START+complete", "A1+complete", "A2+complete", "bE1+complete", "bA9+complete", "bA2+complete", "A3+complete", "tE1+complete", "tA12+complete", "tA2+complete", "A4+complete"]
]

prefix = ["START+complete", "A1+complete", "A2+complete", "bE1+complete", "bA11+complete", "bA2+complete", "A3+complete", "tE1+complete", "tA9+complete", "tA2+complete", "A4+complete"]

next_activity = find_next_activity(past_traces, prefix)
print(next_activity)
```

- Trace 3 partially matches the prefix up to A3+complete but does not include E2+complete which is present in the prefix.
